From: PhantomFPGA Project <phantom@localhost>
Date: Mon, 27 Jan 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] hw/misc: add phantomfpga PCIe device

Add PhantomFPGA, a virtual FPGA device for testing DMA ring buffer
drivers. The device simulates a high-speed frame producer that writes
data to guest memory via DMA, allowing development and testing of
zero-copy streaming drivers without real hardware.

Features:
- PCIe device with MSI-X interrupts
- Configurable DMA ring buffer for frame streaming
- Simulated frame generation at configurable rates
- Host-side watermark interrupts for efficient polling

The device appears as PCI vendor 0x1DAD, device 0xF00D.
Because every good fake FPGA needs a dad joke in its PCI ID.

Signed-off-by: PhantomFPGA Project <phantom@localhost>
---
 hw/misc/Kconfig      | 5 +++++
 hw/misc/meson.build  | 2 ++
 2 files changed, 7 insertions(+)

diff --git a/hw/misc/Kconfig b/hw/misc/Kconfig
index 000000000..111111111 100644
--- a/hw/misc/Kconfig
+++ b/hw/misc/Kconfig
@@ -1,3 +1,8 @@
+config PHANTOMFPGA
+    bool
+    default y if PCI_DEVICES
+    depends on PCI && MSI_NONBROKEN
+
 config APPLESMC
     bool
     depends on ISA_BUS
diff --git a/hw/misc/meson.build b/hw/misc/meson.build
index 000000000..111111111 100644
--- a/hw/misc/meson.build
+++ b/hw/misc/meson.build
@@ -1,3 +1,5 @@
+system_ss.add(when: 'CONFIG_PHANTOMFPGA', if_true: files('phantomfpga.c'))
+
 system_ss.add(when: 'CONFIG_APPLESMC', if_true: files('applesmc.c'))
 system_ss.add(when: 'CONFIG_EDU', if_true: files('edu.c'))
 system_ss.add(when: 'CONFIG_FW_CFG_DMA', if_true: files('vmcoreinfo.c'))
--
